solution.p:
Recall the Hall effect formula,

	B = \dfrac{V_{\perp}}{I}\: n\:e\:w\:h.

Putting the values from the problem statement, we find the Hall voltage  V_{\perp}.

	 V_{\perp} \amp = \dfrac{BI}{n\:e\:w\:h} 
	 \amp= \dfrac{2.5\: \text{T}\times 1.5\:\text{A}}{8.4\times 10^{28}\:\text{m}^{-3}\times 1.6\times 10^{-19}\:\text{C}\times 0.02\:\text{m}\times 0.03\:\text{m}}
	 \amp = 4.65\times 10^{-7}\:\text{V}.

Recall the Hall effect formula,

	B = \dfrac{V_{\perp}}{I}\: n\:e\:w\:h.

Putting the values from the problem statement, we find the Hall voltage  V_{\perp}.

	n \amp = \dfrac{BI}{V_{\perp}\:e\:w\:h} 
	 \amp = \dfrac{3\:  \textrm{T}\times 3\:\textrm{A}}{40\times 10^{-6}\:\textrm{V}\times 1.6\times 10^{-19}\:\textrm{C}\times 0.015\:\textrm{m}\times 0.004\:\textrm{m}}
	 \amp = 2.34\times 10^{28}\:\textrm{m}^{-3}.
